Section 10. Cure Period; Termination
------------------------------------

(a) First-time inadvertent breach. If you cease all breach of this License
    within thirty (30) days of your first receipt of written notice from
    Licensor identifying the breach, your rights under this License are
    automatically reinstated.

(b) Repeat breach. Second and subsequent breaches by you, or by any entity
    controlled by you, controlling you, or under common control with you,
    will result in immediate termination of all rights granted under this
    License, without further notice and without a right of cure.

(c) Material breach without cure. Notwithstanding paragraph (a) of this
    Section 10, any breach of Section 4 (Prohibition on Competing Use),
    Section 6(b) or 6(d) (misrepresentation of authorship or affiliation),
    or Section 9 (Sanctions Compliance and Export Controls), or any
    intentional or willful breach of this License, will result in immediate
    termination of all rights granted under this License, without right of
    cure.

(d) Effect of termination. Upon termination, you shall cease all use of the
    Software, destroy or return all copies of the Software in your
    possession or control, and certify in writing to Licensor that you have
    done so. The provisions of Sections 11 (Grant of Future License), 12
    (Disclaimer of Warranty), 13 (Limitation of Liability), 14 (Governing
    Law; Venue), 15 (General Provisions), and any other provision that by
    its nature should survive termination, shall survive termination of
    this License. Termination of this License does not affect Licensor's
    right to bring legal action for breaches occurring prior to
    termination.

